gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 133, Suns 131
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pacers outscored the Suns, 28-17, in the final quarter as they defeated them, 133-131. Devin Booker led the Suns with a season-high 62 points, along with five rebounds, and four assists as Kevin Durant added 20 points, seven rebounds, and six assists. Pascal Siakam led five Pacers player with 20 or more points with 31 points (14-22 FG), seven rebounds, and four assists as Obi Toppin (23 points, 11 rebounds) and Andrew Nembhard (22 points, eight assists) totaled 45 points. The Pacers improve to 26-20 as the Suns move to 26-19, having their seven-game win streak snapped.
